# Zenode Engine Documentation & Schema Expansion Plan

This document provides a complete reference for the current Zenode Public API and outlines the proposed schema expansion to support advanced properties (rotation, custom plugin metadata) in both JSON and XML formats.

## 1. Exposed Public API Reference

The following table lists the core APIs available via the `Zenode` module or the global `engine` object.

### Lifecycle & Configuration
| API | Description | Usage Example |
|---|---|---|
| `initializeCanvas(selector, config)` | Initializes the engine in the target DOM element. | `Zenode.initializeCanvas('#canvas', { ... })` |
| `updateConfig(config)` | Updates the global engine configuration properties. | `Zenode.updateConfig({ grid: { visible: false } })` |
| `resizeCanvas(w, h)` | Manually resets the canvas dimensions. | `Zenode.resizeCanvas(1920, 1080)` |
| `clear()` | Wipes all nodes and edges from the canvas. | `Zenode.clear()` |

### Node & Edge Management
| API | Description | Usage Example |
|---|---|---|
| `addNode(config)` | Adds a new node to the canvas programmatically. | `Zenode.addNode({ type: 'circle', x: 100, y: 100 })` |
| `removeNode(id)` | Deletes a node and its associated connections. | `Zenode.removeNode('node-123')` |
| `updateNode(id, patch)` | Updates node data (position, metadata). | `Zenode.updateNode('n1', { x: 200 })` |
| `addEdge(config)` | Creates a connection between two node ports. | `Zenode.addEdge({ sourceNodeId: 'n1', targetNodeId: 'n2' })` |
| `duplicateNode(id)` | Clones a node and its current content. | `const newId = Zenode.duplicateNode('n1')` |

### Visuals & Status
| API | Description | Usage Example |
|---|---|---|
| `setNodeStatus(id, type)` | Triggers visual feedback (running, success, error). | `engine.setNodeStatus('n1', 'running')` |
| `updateNodeContent(id, cnt)` | Sets text, icons, and layout for a node. | `Zenode.updateNodeContent('n1', { items: [...] })` |
| `highlight(id, duration)` | Pulses a node to draw user attention. | `engine.highlight('n1', 2000)` |
| `focusNode(id)` | Centers and zooms the viewport on a specific node. | `engine.focusNode('n1')` |

### Serialization & Data
| API | Description | Usage Example |
|---|---|---|
| `toXML()` | Exports current state as a Zenode-schema XML string. | `const xml = Zenode.toXML()` |
| `fromXML(xml)` | Restores the engine state from an XML string. | `Zenode.fromXML(myXmlString)` |
| `toMermaid()` | Generates a Mermaid.js flowchart script. | `console.log(Zenode.toMermaid())` |
| `toDOT()` | Generates a Graphviz DOT representation. | `const dot = Zenode.toDOT()` |
| `validate()` | Runs structural checks (cycles, orphans). | `const results = Zenode.validate()` |

