## 2. Proposed XML/JSON Schema Expansion

To support **Phase 4 (Differentiator Features)**, we need to extend the data model to handle rotation, explicit sizing, and custom plugin metadata.

### Proposed XML Structure
We will adopt a more granular structure that allows for future-proofing and third-party plugin data.

```xml
<zenode:workflow version="3.3">
  <nodes>
    <node id="task1" type="rectangle" x="150" y="200" 
          width="160" height="80" rotation="45">
          
      <!-- Core Content: Serialized from NodeContent -->
      <content layout="icon-top-text">
        <item kind="icon" value="lucide:zap" color="#ff0" />
        <item kind="text" value="High Energy Task" size="14" />
      </content>

      <!-- Advanced Visual State -->
      <status current="running" />
      <effects glow="#3b82f6" intensity="0.8" />

      <!-- Plugin Metadata: Catch-all for non-standard data -->
      <meta>
        <property name="custom:plugin-id">{"key": "value"}</property>
        <property name="execution:timeout">5000</property>
      </meta>
    </node>
  </nodes>
</zenode:workflow>
```

### Proposed JSON Structure (`NodeData` Update)
The JSON structure will mirror the XML changes for parity.

```json
{
  "id": "task1",
  "type": "rectangle",
  "x": 150,
  "y": 200,
  "width": 160,
  "height": 80,
  "rotation": 45,
  "content": {
    "layout": "icon-top-text",
    "items": [ ... ]
  },
  "visualState": {
    "status": "running",
    "effects": { "glow": { "color": "#3b82f6" } }
  },
  "meta": {
    "custom:plugin-id": { "key": "value" },
    "execution:timeout": 5000
  }
}
```

